# Frontend rules (Next.js + shadcn/ui + Supabase SSR + AI SDK)

## Styling + components

- Prefer **Tailwind CSS utility classes** for styling. Avoid custom CSS unless absolutely necessary.
- Prefer reusing existing third-party UI primitives already in this repo (e.g. **shadcn/ui**, **Base UI**, **Radix**) over writing bespoke components.
- When a shadcn/ui component exists for a pattern (Dialog, AlertDialog, DropdownMenu, Form, etc.), use it instead of custom implementations.

## UI vs hooks separation

- UI components go in `src/components/**`.
- Business/data hooks go in `src/hooks/**`.
- Shared clients/env/helpers go in `src/lib/**`.

## Supabase auth (SSR)

- Use `@supabase/ssr` helpers in `src/lib/supabase/*`.
- Route protection is done via `frontend/middleware.ts`.

## Chat integration

- UI uses `@ai-sdk/react` `useChat`.
- Always include `conversation_id` + selected `kb_ids` in request body.
- Call Next.js `POST /api/chat` route handler (it injects Bearer JWT and proxies to backend).

